Method Detail

getAutoTagger

public static AutoTagger getAutoTagger(java.io.File autoTaggerFile)
                                throws java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
This method loads an AutoTagger from the contents of the class file, without regard to the name of the file or the package it is in. It also enables loading a class from a JAR file, given the standard of class with binary name some.package.of.ThisClass should be in a JAR named some.package.of.ThisClass.jar.

Parameters:
autoTaggerFile - File of AutoTagger class to load. Naming doesn't matter as the class is read from binary- for simpler use. AutoTagger implementor can use whichever package he wants.
Returns:
An AutoTagger object from the given class file.
Throws:
java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
